```suggestion
  âŸ¨by simpa only [symm_apply_apply] using Irreducible.map f.symm (x := f a), Irreducible.map fâŸ©
```
Why do you need `change` here? Please try to avoid it
I didn't find lemmas for me to travel between `eval_2` `comp` and `algEquivAevalXAddC`. I'll try to add what I need to Mathlib.

```suggestion
theorem sub_algebraMap {B : Type*} [CommRing B] [Algebra A B] (x : B)
```
for consistency

`split` â†’ `splits`, and the order doesn't make sense to me. Probably `splits_minpoly_{add,sub}_algebraMap`

Do you also want to add the `algebraMap K L r +/- x` variants?

Thank you! I'll rename it to `minpoly_{add, sub}_algebraMap_splits` which is the order of the first four terms that can be read in the conclusion `(minpoly K (x + algebraMap K L r)).Splits (algebraMap K L)`.

I realized that in order to add `algebraMap K L r - x` variant, I need to prepare several lemmas for `minpoly K (-x)` I'll just add `algebraMap K L r + x` in this PR and open a new one for  `algebraMap K L r - x`
